<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1677" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1677">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/688a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Jefferson</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 3, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department approves general principles of contract now being made with
                            bankers but has not had an opportunity to consider details. Hope
                            Congress will adopt system of taxation sufficient to provide for the
                            needs of the Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>